snippet.textDisplay: I dont remember what I was doing  or where I was  the moment i found out Eddie Guerrero died . But I remember  I was in marine corps bootcamp  in June 2007 and my senior killhat (drill instructor ) brought in the news paper and asked us who watches wrestling  ? Then he said chris Benoit is dead .   I know Eddie had struggled with drugs and alcohol  but the way he told a story was  epic.  I have been a long time  wrestling fan and I can't remember  someone  being so over for being a heel lying cheating and stealing  RIP  Eddie  as far as Benoit people judge the Man but  no one knows for sure  how the concussions and steroid abuse affected and traumatized him and his body he was an amazing  wrestler . And rumor was he was supposed to win the ecw  title that night . He no showed . I will always remember  him as one of the most intense  wrestlers on any promotion  I just recently started watching him on njp  (new Japan wrestling) I'm sure he influenced  the Daniel Bryan's of today.  I first watched wcw I remember  him being the Canadian crypler  because  he broke  sabus neck my fav segment  was when he beat Orlando jordan in 32 ? Seconds he  took a piss and made a cup of coffee   benoit could lock  that hold in from any position  and often did so I loved how he made the bigger guys tap to it.

snippet.textDisplay:
I am currently in recovery for a serious opioid addiction. I've posted on other videos about MY situation and have had people try to call me out. The God honest truth is that at the height of my addiction I was taking anywhere from 50 to 200 Norco's a day. I have no reason to lie about that. Basically I would take however many pills I could find that day. I have a VERY HIGH tolerance when it comes to opioids. Thankfully I never did heroin but don't get me wrong I was very close a few times. I have been clean for 3 plus years now with ZERO relapses. I am very proud of that. I try to pay it forward as much as possible and I am proud to say I've helped several people to get help.
My wife was the angel that saved my life. She refused to be an enabler. On her birthday in 2017 she came to me and said that if I don't get help she's taking the kids and leaving. That was enough for me. I tell people that an addict doesn't have to lose everything to hit "rock bottom. Just lose or be threatened with losing that one thing that means the most to you and you will quickly seek help.
So that day I told her I was gonna research it and see what's up. That's when she whipped out her laptop and showed me my options. She had already done the research because, according to her, she knew the threat of losing her and my 2 babies would kill me and that I would make the right decision. Wwweellllll.....here we are. She had already requested the day off and had talked to my boss and let them know the situation.
We choose an outpatient Methadone clinic that was not far from where we lived. After being in that program for more than 3 years I am happy to say that THIS TREATMENT WAS/ IS WHAT WORKS FOR ME!! I hear all kinds of negative stuff about Methadone and what not but it worked/is working for me so I'm sticking with it. I have gone from 185mg a day to 55mg a day today. With the help of the nurses, doctor and my wife & kids I am happy to say THIS METHOD WORKED FOR ME!!! I believe in it and plan the work and work the plan!!!
For anyone out there in that situation please know that there is help and most importantly HOPE!!! It is certainly worth it in the end. I was an athlete for a very long time. I wrestled(Olympic style or freestyle)for 17 years and having my career ended by a jealous former world champion who couldn't take a loss along with several other things contributed to my 6 year "pity party".
The guys in these stories about wrestling go through hell for what they do. Then people discount and say "It's fake. They know how take a fall and/or punch." Really?? Go up and say that to one of them!! You'll get John Stosseled(look it up on YT. It's awesome). Plus if that were the case every MMA and boxing match would end in a draw!!!!
I say all this, and I apologize for the long post but I really wanted to get this out there, to let people know there is help. My addiction started innocently enough. A simple back injury at work and 6 months later I'm hooked!!! Seek the help. I promise you won't be sorry!!! Good luck!!!
Again, I apologize for the long rant but I am just trying to pay it forward anytime I can.
28:37.....That story of Eddie passing out like that gave me goosebumps!! My wife said I would do that all the time. She knew that's when I had done to many pills!!!! Awful!!!

So by default, we should judge him mostly on what we do know and if we did, he’d be in the hall of fame already because of his great work.
